cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.MM

The paper proposes an improved algorithm for aligning temporal sequences, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of dynamic time warping (DTW) suggests that the paper could belong to cs.SD (Sound), while the application of the algorithm to audio, video, and graphics data alignments suggests cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of shapeDTW as a distance measure in a nearest neighbor classifier suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on locally similar structures suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
